history.content:
According to the cs-faq, if you take cs 88 and cs 8, you'll need to take cs47A to substitute for cs 61a. None of those three will count in your cs major declaration gpa however.

Regarding your waitlist chance, cs 61a is hiring staff for the summer right now and might be able to hire more TAs and expand if there's high enrollment.

children.subject: SU20 CS61A just expanded by the way

history.content: I was originally intending a Data Science major, but after taking a few classes, I realized I would like to pursue a CS major or even a double major. I am currently in CS88, which is the equivalent of 61A for the Data Science major. However, for CS, 88 does not satisfy any requirements. I enrolled in 61A for the summer but am #72 out of 75 on the waitlist. I really need to get into this class to be able to satisfy requirements in time. What are my chances of getting off the waitlist into the class? Are there any equivalents to the 61A CS requirement that i may not be aware of? Please advise.
